The paper deals with the computational complexity of the $(k,r)$-Center problem, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and has applications in various fields. The paper provides tight bounds and approximation algorithms for the problem with respect to various structural parameters of the input graph, such as clique-width, treewidth, vertex cover, and tree-depth. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
